name: Josephine
description: Sometimes there was time left in the world to contemplate a place where there were no disasters. Josephine was always there; a distraction to the chaos, an avant-garde peace, something non-existent that materialized in the air, that was drenched in river, rain, cold, warm air and a perfume of freshly cut grass. If you found it there at your feet, then you felt the calm of relief after the war, the arrival of a day that seemed not to come, the pain of feeling a little.
